 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Digital Customer Experience Manager PNM Resources, Inc 10 reviews Albuquerque, NM Remote PNM Resources, Inc 10 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job details Salary $78,196 - $105,564 a year Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Responsible for the short- and long-term strategy, execution and operations of PNMÂ¿s customer digital experience. This includes leading the digital customer experience through strategy development, planning, day-to-day operations and management. 
ESSENTIAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES: 
Leads a customer focused team to design, implement and manage all customer digital experience channels including PNM.com, two-way texting, alerts & notifications
 Builds the customer digitalization strategy, roadmap and management plan with a focus on customer usability, interface design, technical integration, IT coordination and communication content creation 
Develops and manage a digital customer program portfolio to optimize the customer experience, utility expenses, customer savings and associated revenue in alignment with all applicable local, state and federal regulations 
Establishes annual goals, operational plan, and budget to meet or exceed user experience, user participation, transactional and utilization goals 
Utilizes customer management system to research customer inquiries and implement improvements 
Proposes new programs and/or modifications of existing programs based on customer solutions benchmarking, market research and understanding of current and emerging best practices
 Perform market or customer research to recommend strategy changes, including enhancements, new solutions or retiring of existing solutions 
Actively participates in Corporate and Business Unit Strategic Planning
 Ensures customer digitalization strategies and programs are designed, implemented and operated to result in an optimal customer experience, keeping in line with changing regulations, technologies or business strategies
 Leads change management initiatives to develop and improve internal business processes 
Performs monitoring, analysis, inspection and validation of vendor or third-party compliance with expected program or digital solution performance, service levels and terms and conditions 
COMPETENCIES: 
Ability to strategically approach issues 
Ability to be proactive, adept at working with cross-functional teams and stakeholder groups 
Ability to coordinate with, and lead, cross-functional teams of technical experts 
QUALIFICATIONS 
MINIMUM EDUCATION AND/OR EXPERIENCE: 
Bachelor's degree from four-year college or university in a digital related field with seven to nine years related experience, or equivalent combination of education and/or experience related to the discipline, or equivalent professional certifications and experience. 
Experience in leading and managing customer experiences, and customer service improvement outcomes in various industries. 
Experience with digital customer usability and customer experience principles and best practices, designing digital web platforms, implementing user interfaces and expertise in digital customer communication processes and programs. Understanding of web and app platforms, web development, customer/user experience, alerts and notification platforms and Artificial Intelligence solutions.
 Information Technology, Business Computer Systems, Business Administration of Marketing, Computer Science or / Master's degree preferred. 
SUPERVISORY RESPONSIBILITIES: 
Responsible for the direction of analysts and technical leads of the department 
COMMUNICATION SKILLS: 
Ability to interpret a variety of instructions furnished in written, oral, diagram, or schedule form 
MATHEMATICAL SKILLS: 
Ability to apply concepts such as fractions, percentages, ratios, and proportions to practical situations 
COMPUTER SKILLS: 
Working knowledge of database software, inventory software, spreadsheet, and word processing software 
ANALYSIS AND PROBLEM-SOLVING ABILITY:
 Ability to synthesize complex information. Ability to apply creativity to problem solving and utilize analytic skills and modeling capabilities to provide ongoing insight into the business and to make recommendations and decisions. Ability to identify and develop remediation or mitigation plans as necessary.
 DECISION MAKING: 
Conducts, coordinates, and guides the Digital Solution Strategy, policy, standard and procedure development activities and practices within established risk criteria and in accordance with generally accepted information security standards and regulatory requirements. 
SCOPE AND IMPACT: 
Responsible for driving self-serve utilization to decrease operational costs. 
PHYSICAL DEMANDS: 
While performing the duties of this job, the employee is regularly required to sit up to 2/3 of the time. Manual dexterity and good vision required. The employee must occasionally lift and/or move up to 10 pounds. 
WORK ENVIRONMENT:
 Office environment 
Employees in Services Company may be responsible for providing services to various Holding Company subsidiaries and affiliates. 
 
